2. Sealed Classes
3. Records
4. Switch Expressions
5. Text Blocks

Some Minor Language Features
    Helpful NullPointerExceptions (JEP 358):
	•	Improved diagnostics when a NullPointerException occurs.
	•	Provides better context in exception messages.
    This feature doesn’t need code, but in Java 17, a NullPointerException provides a more informative message. If the following code throws an exception:
	Local Variable var in Lambda Parameters (JEP 361):
	•	Can use var in lambda expressions to improve consistency.
        (var a, var b) -> a + b;